        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 26 at 4:57PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 457 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Edmore, or 10 miles north of Stanton, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Alma...                St. Louis...           Edmore...
Lakeview...            Crystal...             Sumner...
Millbrook...           McBride...             Westville...
Elm Hall...            Cedar Lake...          Six Lakes...
Gratiot Community Ai...Vestaburg...           Blanchard...
Forest Hill...         Riverdale...           Wyman...
Winn...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
